Six people have been killed in separate incidents in just over a week. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Communist Party (SACP) believes a hit squad is operating in KwaZulu-Natal to target its members.Six people have been killed in separate incidents in just over a week.The party says it s provisionally agreed with the KwaZulu-Natal government to set up a satellite police station in Inchanga, in the wake of the political killings.No arrest have been made but a police team continues to probe the murders.The second secretary of the SACP, Solly Mapaila, says: Government has been considering the possibility of setting up a satellite police station, as agreed in the meeting that it should be set up. People are just being hit and they don t know who hit them. They re able to get away with it because there isn t sufficient police presence in the area. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)